                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d870">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.1928/384: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-28T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >May 28, 1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:56 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>65. The Minister for Foreign Affairs stated to me this morning that practically
                    everything had been agreed upon in the proposed general treaty except the
                    question of deportees which, he remarked, his Government would insist upon being
                    taken care of in the treaty.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
